How would you keep track of the current largest and smallest values while reading the numbers?

This is a classic interview problem and teaches an important pattern used everywhere in data processing and AI pipelines.


Pass count, three fail count two
First, I will take input from the user, then create two loops if I greater than N then n equal to i if not move to the next number and then iterate the cycle, tell you finish the comparison of the last number. Also, you will get the greater number.
Same for minimum if I smaller than N then an equal to I, if not smaller, move to the next number and the same iteration till you reach the last number, comparison.

Good. Your answer shows you're starting to think in terms of **state tracking**, which is exactly what we want.

